-- Apple Says Fair Labor Association Begins Inspections of Foxconn
-- B y   W i l l   D a l e y
-- 2012-02-13T13:34:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/apple-says-fair-labor-group-starts-inspecting-suppliers-including-foxconn.html
Apple Inc. (AAPL)  said the Fair Labor
Association will conduct special voluntary audits of Apple’s
final assembly suppliers, including Foxconn factories in
Shenzhen and Chengdu,  China , at Apple’s request.  A team of labor rights experts led by FLA president Auret
van Heerden began the first inspections this morning at the
facility in Shenzhen known as Foxconn City, Cupertino,
California-based Apple said today in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Daley at 
 wdaley2@bloomberg.net  